Ronaldo Folegatti (April 30, 1958, Rio de Janeiro  – August 1, 2007, Teresópolis) was a Brazilian composer, guitarist, and record producer.
He released his first album, Sound of Watercolors, in Germany in 1990.
Five years later two more albums came out, Mazy Tales and Anjos & Estrellas.
In 2005 he released Jamming!, with guest appearances by Randy Brecker, Will Lee, Joel Rosenblatt  Zé Canuto, Teo Lima, Marcelo Martins, and Ada Rovatti.
During the next two years he was treated for cancer.
He died in 2007, leaving four albums unfinished and unreleased.
